<header> 
<img class="logo" src="assets/groove.png" /> <div class="header-buttons"> <span class="header-button" id='timer'>TIMER </span> <br>   <span id='about' class="header-button"> HOW TO</span> </div>
</header>
  <div class="small-1 columns">
    <main>

      <div class="timer-container"> 
        <h2 class="title"> {{statement}} </h2>
          <button id="fifteen" class="timer-button" ng-click="buttonClicked(15); changeStatement(15)">15 minutes </button>
          <button class= "timer-button" ng-click="buttonClicked(25); changeStatement(25)">25 minutes </button>
          <button class="timer-button" ng-click="buttonClicked(45); changeStatement(45)">45 minutes </button>
          <div flip-Clock> </div>
          <button class="flat-ui-button" ng-click="startClicked()"> Start</button>
          <button id="stop-button" class="timer-button " ng-click="stopClicked()">Stop </button>
          <div ng-click="adjustTime('add'); changeStatement('add');" class="timerButtonContainer addButton"> <div class="upvote"> </div></div>
          <div ng-click="adjustTime('down'); changeStatement('down');"class="timerButtonContainer"> <div class="downvote"> </div></div>
      </div>  



  <div class="small-12 columns" >
         <ng-slide-push-menu position="right" button="push" button-icon-class="glyphicon glyphicon-cog">
        <span><div class="todo-title">My To Do List</div></span>
        <div ng-controller="TodoCtrl">
          <ul>
            <div ng-mouseover="editing = true"  ng-mouseleave="editing = false" class="todo-item" ng-class="{fader:fadeout}" ng-repeat="todo in model.todos" >
                <span>
                  <img class="img-checkmark"   ng-mouseover="completeTask = true" ng-click="fadeout = true; archive(todo);" ng-class="{opacitychange:completeTask}"  ng-mouseleave="completeTask = false" src="assets/checkmark2.png"/>
                  <form class="todo-item-margin noshadow" ng-show="editing" ng-submit="editing = false">
                    <input class="todo-inline-edit noshadow" type="text" ng-model="todo.text">
                  </form>
                  <span  class="todo-item-margin" ng-hide="editing">{{todo.text}}</span>
                  <img ng-show="editing" class ="todo-cancel-button todo-item-margin" ng-click="removeTask($index, todo.text)" src="assets/cancel.png"/>

                </span>
            </div>
          </ul>
          <form ng-submit="addTodo($index)" >
            <input class="todo-item todo-input noshadow" maxlength="25" type="text" ng-model="todoText" size="30"
            placeholder="Add New Item...">
          </form>
        </div>
        </ng-slide-push-menu>
     </div>
        <div class="overlay" ng-show="overlay1"> <div class="overlay-exit" ng-click="exitOverlay(1)">X</div><span class="overlay-text"> Did you complete your task successfully? </span>
            <button ng-click ="secondOverlay(); add();"class="flat-ui-button overlay-button-yes"> Yes, I Did!</button> <button class="timer-button overlay-button-no" ng-click="closeOverlay(); checkProgress();":>No, Not this Time</button>
        </div>
        <div class="overlay2" ng-show="overlay2"> 
        <div class="overlay-exit" ng-click="exitOverlay(2)">X</div>
            <img src="assets/smiley.png" class="overlay-image-smiley"/>
            <span class="overlay-text second-overlay-text"> Congrats, you're one step closer to being done!</span>
        </div>

      <div> 
      </div>
     </main>

    <div class="progress-bar-container">
        <div class="daily-counter"> <div class="daily-count">{{counter}}</div><div class="daily-name">Today </div></div>
        <div progress-bar></div>
        <div class="image-container">
          <img src="assets/teacup.png" id ="teacup-image" class="progress-bar-image"/>
          <span class="progress-bar-image-caption image-caption-teacup"> short break</span>
          <img src="assets/meditate.png" id ="meditate-image" class="progress-bar-image"/>
          <span class="progress-bar-image-caption image-caption-meditate"> short break</span>
          <img src="assets/snack.png" id ="snack-image" class="progress-bar-image"/>
          <span class="progress-bar-image-caption image-caption-snack"> short break</span>
          <img src="assets/bench.png" id ="bench-image" class="progress-bar-image"/>
          <span class="progress-bar-image-caption image-caption-bench"> long break</span>
        </div>
    </div>
<div class="how-to-container">
  <div class="panel">
    <div class="carrot carrot1"></div>
    <div class="panel-main">
      <h1 class="panel-centered-title"> HOW IT WORKS </h1>
      <div class="panel-text">
        GrooveOtter is based off a 30 year  technique to help people be more productive by managing tasks in small intervals. Harness the power of productivity. Find your Groove. 
      </div>
    </div> 
  </div>
  <div class="panel light-green"> 
      <div class="body-position-left">
        <h3 class="white-text"> 1. CHOOSE A TASK TO ACCOMPLISH </h3>
        <p class=" white-text"> Do you need to finish writing that line of code, design out an icon, write a blog post, or study for a test? Choose any number of tasks to work on and we’ll be there to keep you on track.</p>
        <img id="notes" src="assets/notes.png" class="right-panel-image"/>
      </div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel blue">
    <div class="carrot carrot2"></div>
      <img src="assets/flipclock.png"  class="left-panel-image"/>
      <div class="body-position-right">
      <h3 class="white-text "> 2. SET THE TIMER </h3>
      <p class="white-text">Pick one of our predetermined amounts of time scientifically proven to improve mental agility or  input a custom time of your own. Whatever time you choose we’ll make sure you stick to it.  </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel light-blue" id="panel3"> 
    <div class="carrot carrot3"></div>
    <div class="body-position-left">
      <h3 class="white-text "> 2. WORK UNTIL THE TIME IS UP </h3>
      <p class="white-text"> Continue working removed from distractions and without a break until you hear the timer go off. </p>
    </div>
    <img src="assets/time-clock.png" id="time-clock" class="right-panel-image"/>
  </div>
  <div class="panel yellow" id="panel4"> 
    <div class="carrot carrot4"></div>
    <img src="assets/panel-checkmark.png" class="left-panel-image"/>
    <div class="body-position-right">
      <h3 class="white-text ">3. Check it off your list  </h3>
      <p class="white-text"> If you completed your task tell GrooveOtter, watch the progress bar grow, check it off your list, and move on to the next. That felt good right? </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel red" id="panel5"> 
    <div class="carrot carrot5"></div>
    <div class="body-position-left"> 
      <h3 class="white-text">4. Take a 5 minute break </h3>
      <p class="white-text"> You worked hard. Enjoy a short break. Spend it how you like or use one of our recommended breaks.  </p>
    </div>
    <img src="assets/panel-teacup.png" class="right-panel-image"/>
  </div>
  <div class="panel light-green" id="panel6"> 
    <div class="carrot carrot6"></div>
      <img src="assets/panel-smiley.png" class="left-panel-image"/> 
      <div class="body-position-right"> 
        <h3 class="white-text"> 5. Every 4 cycles take a longer break</h3>
        <p class="white-text"> If you complete 4 successful tasks take a longer break.</p>
      </div>
    </div> 
  </div> 
</div>
